<dl id="n53122o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53122o">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53122o"> 122(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> teach to / wear bracelets <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53122o"><li>FW 60.17 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n53122o">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n53122o">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53122o">MS BL 47476b-177</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:375 <a name="cd10" href="../../FF/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n53122o">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Un jour qu&apos;il jouait dans un jardin, pr&egrave;s de la ville, Mah&acirc;praj&acirc;pat&icirc; pensa: &laquo;<mark>Il est temps de lui apprendre &agrave; porter des bracelets</mark> et des colliers.&raquo; Et les servantes furent chercher les parures qu&apos;on lui avait offertes. Mah&acirc;praj&acirc;pat&icirc; les lui mit au bras et au cou, mais il ne semblait pas qu&apos;il en e&ucirc;t aucune; l&apos;or ni les pierres ne brillaient, tant &eacute;clatait la lumi&egrave;re qui &eacute;manait de l&apos;enfant royal. <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 22</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Mahaprajapati at one time taught the boy to wear bracelets, but so dull did these look in contrast to his beauty and vitality she cast them away. </mm> </dd></dl>
